HEADWORD: Self-positing
<hw>Self`-pos"it*ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>The act of disposing or
arranging one's self or itself.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>self-positing</qex> of the molecules.</q> <rj><qau>R.
Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Self-possessed</ent>⟦br⟧
